Discourse Markers Among all kinds of information that may be found in a piece of discourse, discourse markers (also known as discourse connectives, clue words (Reichman 1978; Siegel et al.1994) or cue phrases (Grosz et al.1986; Litman 1996) are regarded as the major linguistic deviceavailable for a writer to structure a discourse.
